Package: rstatic
Title: Primitives to Generate Static SpatioTemporal Asset Catalogs
Version: 0.3.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Rolf", "Simoes",
             email = "rolfsimoes@gmail.com",
             role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Felipe", "Carlos",
             email = "efelipecarlos@gmail.com",
             role = c("aut")),
      person("Felipe", "Souza",
             email = "lipecaso@gmail.com",
             role = c("aut")))
Description: Provides reusable primitives to build and serialize static
    SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog (STAC) documents, including catalogs,
    collections, items, assets, and links. The package implements the STAC
    specification version 1.0.0
    (<https://github.com/radiantearth/stac-spec>) and is intended as a
    foundation for other tools, such as STAC generators and experiment
    catalog builders. Optional spatial metadata extraction and thumbnail
    rendering are supported through 'terra', and 'QGIS' style parsing
    through 'xml2', when these packages are available.
